		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Damage vs Speed! Which weapons to pick?<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Jan 24th 11:08 PM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=98037751919558&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=98037751919558&num=4&page=&post=1&replyto=98037751919558"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=98037751919558></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=17094"><span id=Sage>Kneesmasher</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>397 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.55]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Okay all you Paladins out there, I thought I would start a new thread and get everyone's opinion on the subject of damage of a weapon versus speed of a weapon. While I think we all agree that there is a subjective line, somewhere out there, where damage vs speed is a trade off! The trick is to maximize that trade-off with the right weapons. Since there are few high damage weapons with short delays, you have to make a decision eventually regarding which weapon you want to use, and there are lots to choose from.&nbsp;&nbsp;To start the ball rolling, I will begin with my current arsenal of weapons.<br><br>(1)Deepwater Harpoon: 18 damage, 40 delay, +5 wisdom, +5 stamina, weight of 13, damage per second rating: 9.25. I hit in the upper 30's to mid 40's with this weapon regularly at 30th lvl.  The Wisdom plus is nice and since it's 2-hs and kinda heavy the stamina is always a plus! No doubt about it, it is a nice well-rounded pally only weapon! It is my primary 2-hs weapon. <br><br>(2)2-handed Practice Sword: 19 damage, 47 delay, Weight 10, damage per second rating: 8.30, Procs Shield of Thistles!  I like this weapon, even though it is on the slow side, because it hits like a ton of bricks and procs the damage shield! I hit in the mid 50's with this weapon regularly, even though it is only one damage point more than the Harpoon.  I use this weapon when there is a very good chance of fighting multiple mobs where you will be getting hit from all sides. This works well with lower lvl mobs that swarm but not so well on higher ones. I will probably sell this weapon soon.<br><br>I prefer to fight 2-h slash, and I used the Axe of the Ironback for 10+ lvls and finally moved on;<br>but as we all know, there are lots of times where a BASH is necessary and 1-hs is the way to go. My current 1-hs weapon is: (and YES, that's singular):<br><br>Ghoulbane: Damage 15, Delay 34, Weight 9.5, Damage per second: 9.12, Special Proc of Dismiss Undead!  I use this weapon exclusively for my 1-hs duties.  When fighting undead, there is no equal, at least not that can be attained at my level. The Dismiss Undead Procs for 152 points at lvl 30, along with your regular slash.  I have actually had the sword proc TWICE back to back on a double attack where I did 342 pts of damage to the poor Carrion Ghoul in a single round!  I regularly hit in the mid 30's with this weapon. It is a good 1-hs weapon all around, no doubt about it, and against undead, WATCH OUT! I will keep it til I have to turn it in on my Fiery Avenger/Defender quest, whichever it is. And then I will go back and attempt to get another one! <br><br>My ultimate 1-hs, at least for the foreseeable future, is a Wurmslayer, but I can't realistically afford that yet. My ultimate 2-hs for the foreseeable future is a Mithril 2-hander but I can't afford that either! <br><br>Okay, let the discussion begin! I would like to preface the discussion by: LETS BE REALISTIC! I don't want to hear about how you got a Jade Inlaid Crescent Axe at 7th lvl and it's awesome, or how you used to use Ghoulbane while in your teens but you traded it for a Wurmslayer at 19th and are now looking for a weapon that does over 30 pts of damage since you are now 23rd level!  If you EARNED your weapons, I'd like to hear from you!  Looking forward to the discussion....<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>30th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >4 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
